s quite favorably with several existing multiple testing procedures\navailable in the literature in terms of overall misclassification probability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Mar 2015 05:41:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 16 Dec 2017 22:07:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 15 Jul 2018 19:38:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-17"}
