ian systems are slightly more\nprone to instability. We also add remarks on numerics (a different code is used\nthan in previous papers), on the resemblance of dependence of the dynamics on\nperturbing mass and on orbital energy, on the difference between the Newtonian\nand relativistic Bach--Weyl rings, and on the relation between Poincar\\'e\nsections and orbital shapes within the meridional plane.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Mar 2015 15:10:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-29"}
